library(ggplot2)
df_base <- read.csv("data_base.csv") %>% mutate(group="Base")
df_deathcost1 <- read.csv("data_climber_deathcost_mul1.csv") %>% mutate(group="DeathCost-1")
df_deathcost2 <- read.csv("data_deathcostminus10.csv") %>% mutate(group="DeathCost-2")
df <- rbind(df_base,df_deathcost1,df_deathcost2)
df

Steps: 1000 

df %>%
  mutate(Death = (Steps < 1000 & ExtReward == 0 )) %>% 
  mutate(GameClear = (ExtReward > 0)) -> df
df_status <- df
surv_obj <- Surv(time = df_status$Steps, event = df_status$Death)
fit <- survfit(surv_obj ~ group, data = df_status)

# 
ggsurvplot(
  fit,
  data = df_status,
  pval = TRUE,              # p
  conf.int = TRUE,          # 
  risk.table = TRUE,        # 
  xlab = "Step",   # x
  ylab = "Survival Probability", # y
  title = "Kaplan-Meier Survival Curve" # 
)

-10 GLOBAL STEP 

df <- df %>%
  mutate(
    Era = case_when(
      Step <= 10000000 ~ "First",
      Step <= 20000000 ~ "Second",
      TRUE ~ "Last"
    )
  )
df_status <- df %>% filter(Era=="First")
surv_obj <- Surv(time = df_status$Steps, event = df_status$Death)
fit <- survfit(surv_obj ~ group + Era, data = df_status)

# 
ggsurvplot(
  fit,
  data = df_status,
  pval = TRUE,              # p
  conf.int = TRUE,          # 
  risk.table = FALSE,        # 
  xlab = "Step",   # x
  ylab = "Survival Probability", # y
  title = "Kaplan-Meier Survival Curve" # 
) 

df_status <- df %>% filter(Era=="Second")

Base.

Era(Step)

StepCox

df_cox <- df %>% 
  filter(group=="Base") %>% 
  mutate(Step = Step * 1e-6 ) %>% 
  mutate(Step2 = Step*Step )%>%
  mutate(Step3 = Step*Step*Step )
# Cox
cox_model <- coxph(Surv(time = Steps, event = Death) ~ Step + Step2 + Step3 , data = df_cox)
summary(cox_model)
## Call:
## coxph(formula = Surv(time = Steps, event = Death) ~ Step + Step2 + 
##     Step3, data = df_cox)
## 
##   n= 177627, number of events= 66790 
## 
##             coef  exp(coef)   se(coef)      z Pr(>|z|)    
## Step   4.638e-01  1.590e+00  6.756e-03  68.65   <2e-16 ***
## Step2 -2.132e-02  9.789e-01  4.337e-04 -49.17   <2e-16 ***
## Step3  2.747e-04  1.000e+00  8.409e-06  32.66   <2e-16 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

##       exp(coef) exp(-coef) lower .95 upper .95

## Step2    0.9789     1.0216    0.9781    0.9797
## Step3    1.0003     0.9997    1.0003    1.0003
## 
## Concordance= 0.65  (se = 0.001 )
## Likelihood ratio test= 17983  on 3 df,   p=<2e-16
## Wald test            = 12687  on 3 df,   p=<2e-16
## Score (logrank) test = 14329  on 3 df,   p=<2e-16
ggforest(cox_model, data = df_cox)

# Step
step_range <- seq(min(df_cox$Step), max(df_cox$Step), length.out = 100)

# 
hazard_data <- data.frame(
  Step = step_range,
  HazardRatio = exp(coef(cox_model)["Step"] * step_range + coef(cox_model)["Step2"] * step_range^2 + coef(cox_model)["Step3"] * step_range^3)
)

# 
ggplot(hazard_data, aes(x = Step, y = HazardRatio)) +
  geom_line(color = "blue", size = 1) +
  labs(
    title = "Hazard Ratio vs Step",
    x = "Step1.0e-6",
    y = "Hazard Ratio"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    text = element_text(size = 12)
  )
